Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Trim the @aubergine{1%unit}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1%unit}. Peel the @garlic{3%cloves}(whole).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry until soft and
sweet, ~{10-12%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Meanwhile, pop the aubergine, pepper strips, @baby plum tomatoes{190%g} and garlic
cloves onto a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @dried basil{1%sachet}, then season with salt
and pepper. Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer (use two trays if necessary).

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the aubergine is soft and golden
~{18-20%minutes}.

Once the onion has softened, pour the @water{240%ml}(for the bulgur wheat) into a
#large saucepan{}, stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for
~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

When the veg is cooked, remove from your oven and lightly crush both the garlic and
the tomatoes with the back of a #fork{}.

Gently stir to combine the veg on the tray.

When the bulgur wheat is cooked, stir through two thirds of the @fresh pesto{50%g}.
Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Share the pesto bulgur wheat between your #bowls{}.

Top with the roasted ratatouille, @diced chorizo{90%g} and drizzle with the remaining
pesto.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}. Sprinkle over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g}.

Enjoy!